    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <head>No. 588.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Cushing</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 24,
                                    1875</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have submitted to President your note of 11th, and Castro’s of 15th, as
                            received by cable. He approves of agreement as therein proposed. You
                            will telegraph fact and date of signature, and, so soon as credentials
                            are received and presented, will sign final agreement, and immediately
                            telegraph the fact.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
